<p>When people think about open source hardware, they often think about the general category of electronics that can be soldered and needs batteries. While there are <a href="https://certification.oshwa.org/list.html">many</a> fantastic open source pieces of electronics, the overall category of open source hardware is much broader. This month we take a look at open source hardware that you can take out into the world, no power outlet or batteries required.</p>

<h2 id="hummingbird-hammocks">Hummingbird Hammocks</h2>

<p><a href="https://hummingbirdhammocks.com/">Hummingbird Hammocks</a> offers an entire line of open source camping gear. You can set up an open source <a href="https://certification.oshwa.org/us000102.html">rain tarp</a>â€¦</p>

<p><img src="/images/hummingbird_hammocks_rain_tarp.png" alt="Tarp Picture" /></p>

